:: StoryTitle
The Girl and the Dust


:: StoryData
{
  "ifid": "B2C3D4E5-F6A7-8901-BCDE-FA2345678901",
  "format": "Harlowe",
  "format-version": "3.3.8",
  "start": "Start",
  "zoom": 1
}


:: Arrival at Bolvangar {"position":"2000,200","size":"100,100"}



Bolvangar: a concrete-and-metal compound planted in endless white. Wire fences, floodlights, guards. It looks like a prison disguised as a school.

(if: $hasDocs is true)[
Lyra remembers the documents from Jordan's cellars. This didn't start here. They've been experimenting for decades. The horror has deep roots.
]

Pan shifts to a white ermine, vanishing against the snow. *"We need to get inside without being seen."*

Lyra spots a ventilation shaft on the building's side. She also sees a service door with a single guard.

[[Crawl through the ventilation shaft->Ventilation Infiltration]]
[[Distract the guard and slip through the door->Door Infiltration]]


:: Billy Costa {"position":"1500,250","size":"100,100"}

(set: $sawBilly to true)

In a dark corner of the ship, Lyra finds a boy sitting alone. Billy Costa, Ma Costa's son. He was rescued days ago, but something is terribly wrong.

Billy clutches a piece of dried fish against his chest, holding it the way you'd hold a dæmon. But there is no dæmon beside him. They performed the **intercision**.

*"Where's Ratter?"* he murmurs, voice hollow. *"Where's my Ratter?"*

Pan retreats to Lyra's chest, and she holds him so tight it hurts. Seeing a child without their dæmon is like seeing someone whose soul has been ripped out and left an empty shape behind.

*"Lyra,"* says Pan, his voice shaking, *"we have to stop this. Whatever it costs."*

Lyra doesn't cry. She clenches her fists.

(set: $panState to "determined")

[[Return to the ship->The Gyptian Ship]]


:: Bittersweet Ending {"position":"3800,300","size":"100,100"}

# The Price of Rescue

Lyra got Roger out of Bolvangar. But not all the children. Some were left behind, and the weight of it sits like a stone on her chest.

Roger walks beside her in silence. Snow crunches underfoot.

(if: (history:) contains "Too Late")[
Roger is not the same. He stares at the horizon with empty eyes, searching for something that's no longer there. Sometimes he calls for Salcilia in his sleep.

Lyra takes his hand and doesn't let go. She can't undo what happened. But she can be here.

Pan shifts constantly — cat, bird, mouse — restless, reflecting Lyra's guilt.
](else:)[
Roger holds Salcilia tight against his chest. *"Lyra, will we go back for the others?"*

*"Yes,"* says Lyra. And she means it.

Pan takes the shape of a fox: sharp, watchful, ready for whatever comes.
]

The lights of Bolvangar die behind them. The aurora keeps burning.

Lyra looks north. The journey is not over.


END — The Bittersweet Path
Good intentions are not always enough. But Lyra doesn't give up.



:: Bolvangar Doors {"position":"2450,200","size":"100,100"}


The corridors of Bolvangar are white, lit by a fluorescent hum. Every door looks the same. Pan sniffs the air in dog form.

*"I can't tell which way, Lyra. This whole place smells of fear."*

Lyra picks a door at random and pushes it open...

(goto: (either: "Children's Dormitory", "Empty Laboratory", "Bolvangar Office"))


:: Bolvangar Office {"position":"2600,300","size":"100,100"}

An elegant study that doesn't belong in this place. A fur coat hangs on the rack. A perfume Lyra recognizes instantly.

*"Mrs Coulter,"* Pan whispers. *"She's here."*

(if: $coulterRoute is true)[
A shudder runs through Lyra. She remembers the golden monkey seizing Pan, the paperweight, the desperate flight through London.

*"This time I'm ready,"* she says.
]

On the desk: maps of the North, lists of children's names, and a report titled *"Phase 3 Results: Complete Intercision."* The data is cold, clinical. It speaks of children as numbers.

(set: $allies to $allies + 1)

[[Find Roger->Finding Roger]]
[[Try another door->Bolvangar Doors]]


:: Call for Help {"position":"3200,200","size":"100,100"}

(set: $panState to "desperate")

Lyra sprints to the nearest window and screams with everything she has: *"GYPTIANS!! HERE!! THE CHILDREN ARE HERE!!"*

Pan launches himself through the window as a hawk, shrieking.

(if: $allies >= 4)[
The gyptians, who'd surrounded the station waiting for the signal, burst in through every entrance. John Faa leads the charge.

The guard holding Roger flees in the chaos. Lyra pulls him free from the cage.

*"Just in time!"* Roger says, tears streaming down his face.
](else:)[
The gyptians are too few. The response comes slowly. By the time they arrive, Lyra has had to fight the guard alone, and Roger has a cut on his forehead.

But they're alive. And together.
]

[[Get all the children out!->The Escape]]


:: Chase Scene {"position":"2300,300","size":"100,100"}

Lyra sprints through the snow, heart hammering. Pan flies ahead as a swallow. Guards shout behind her.

*"There!"* Pan screams, diving toward a gap under the fence.

Lyra slides through, scraping her palms raw, and clambers in through a broken basement window.

She's inside. But they know someone's here. She'll have to move fast.

(set: $panState to "frantic")

[[Find the children->Bolvangar Doors]]


:: Children's Dormitory {"position":"2600,100","size":"100,100"}

The door opens onto a large room filled with small beds. Dozens of children, all clutching their dæmons close. Some sleep. Some stare at the ceiling with eyes that have seen too much.

A girl approaches. *"Are you new? Don't let them take you upstairs. The ones who go up... come back wrong."*

Lyra scans the faces. No Roger.

*"Do you know a boy called Roger?"*

*"Roger's in the other room. End of the corridor."*

[[Go find Roger->Finding Roger]]
[[Try another door->Bolvangar Doors]]


:: Consult Alethiometer Ship {"position":"1500,450","size":"100,100"}


Lyra finds a quiet corner and takes out the alethiometer. The needles swing and settle on three symbols: **the Baby**, **the Skull**, and **(either: "the Beehive", "the Anchor", "the Candelabrum")**.

She closes her eyes. Concentrates. The images flow...

[[The children are in mortal danger at Bolvangar — there's no time left->Correct Reading 2]]
[[The Gobblers have a secret underwater base->Wrong Reading 2]]


:: Correct Reading 1 {"position":"700,300","size":"100,100"}

(set: $accuracy to $accuracy + 1)

A certainty floods through Lyra that she can't explain. The needles tremble — almost as if they're nodding.

Pan stares at her. *"Are you sure?"*

*"Yes,"* Lyra says. *"Sure as breathing."*

Something is changing in her. She's learning to read the alethiometer in a way no one taught her. As if the instrument recognizes something within her.

[[Back to the rooftops->Jordan Rooftops]]


:: Correct Reading 2 {"position":"1650,400","size":"100,100"}

(set: $accuracy to $accuracy + 1)

The long needle shudders to a halt, confirming. Lyra feels ice in her veins.

*"They're doing terrible things there, Pan,"* she says. *"And Roger is among them."*

Pan's eyes harden. *"Then we get there in time."*

[[Return to the ship->The Gyptian Ship]]


:: Create Distraction {"position":"3200,300","size":"100,100"}

Lyra grabs a bottle of chemicals from a shelf and hurls it at the machine's instruments. Glass shatters. Liquid hisses and smokes. The technicians scramble backward.

Pan darts across the guard's face as a swallow, blinding him.

*"ROGER, RUN!"* Lyra screams.

Roger scrambles out of the cage, clutching Salcilia to his chest. Smoke fills the laboratory.

*"This way!"* Lyra drags him into the corridor.

[[We have to escape!->The Escape]]


:: Departure North {"position":"1800,200","size":"100,100"}

The gyptian fleet sails north. Days grow shorter, nights longer. The aurora borealis drapes the sky in curtains of green and violet.

(if: $knowsMotherTruth is true)[
Lyra watches the lights and thinks about Mrs Coulter. *"How can someone capable of such terrible things be my mother, Pan?"*

Pan presses against her neck. *"You don't have to be like her, Lyra. You choose who you are."*
](else:)[
Lyra gazes up in wonder. *"It's the most beautiful thing I've ever seen, Pan."*

Pan nods in ermine form. *"Beautiful and dangerous. Like everything up north."*
]

After days of travel, the lookouts spot metal structures rising from the snow. **Bolvangar**.

[[Approach Bolvangar->Arrival at Bolvangar]]


:: Destroy Machine {"position":"3200,100","size":"100,100"}

(set: $panState to "fierce")

Lyra hurls herself at the machine. She tears at the controls, rips cables, throws levers. Pan, transformed into a snarling wildcat, flings himself at the golden monkey.

Sparks. Smoke. A shriek of metal.

The blade stops centimetres from Roger. The machine dies.

Roger collapses, trembling, Salcilia pressed to his chest. Together. Still together.

*"Lyra..."* he gasps.

No time for embraces. The alarm is screaming through the entire station.

[[We need to run — now!->The Escape]]


:: Door Infiltration {"position":"2150,300","size":"100,100"}


(set: $dice to (random: 1, 6))

Lyra picks up a stone and hurls it into the darkness. The guard turns his head.

(if: $dice >= 3)[
He walks off to investigate. Lyra slips through the door like a shadow.

*"Nicely done,"* Pan murmurs.

[[Explore the corridors->Bolvangar Doors]]

](else:)[
The stone hits the wall too close. The guard spins around and spots her.

*"Halt! Who's there?"*

(set: $allies to $allies - 1)
(if: $allies < 0)[(set: $allies to 0)]

[[Run->Chase Scene]]
]


:: Eavesdrop Scholars {"position":"550,50","size":"100,100"}

Lyra crawls across the rooftops to a skylight above the Dean's office. Voices drift up through the glass.

*"...the Gobblers are moving closer to Oxford..."*
*"...Mrs Coulter arrives within days..."*
*"...we cannot allow her to take the girl..."*

Pan's fur bristles. *"Are they talking about you?"*

Lyra isn't sure. But something shifts inside her — the first pull of a thread she won't be able to stop pulling.

(set: $allies to $allies + 1)

[[Back to the rooftops->Jordan Rooftops]]


:: Empty Laboratory {"position":"2600,200","size":"100,100"}

A room full of scientific instruments, monitors beeping in steady rhythm. At its centre stands a metal structure shaped like a cage, divided into two compartments. One for a child. One for their dæmon.

The **intercision machine**.

Pan presses against Lyra's chest, shaking. *"Lyra, this is — this is where they do it."*

(if: $sawBilly is true)[
Lyra thinks of Billy Costa, clutching a piece of dried fish where his dæmon should be. Rage burns through her like fire.

*"We're going to destroy this thing,"* she says, her voice like steel.
](else:)[
It takes Lyra a moment to understand what she's seeing. When she does, the horror is so vast she can't speak.

*"Pan..."* is all she manages.
]

[[Keep searching for Roger->Finding Roger]]
[[Try another door->Bolvangar Doors]]


:: Escape Failed {"position":"3550,400","size":"100,100"}

Guards cut off the corridor. Lyra and the children are trapped.

Then Ma Costa bursts through a side door with a squad of armed gyptians. *"This way, children!"*

They escape — barely. Some children don't make it out.

(goto: "Bittersweet Ending")


:: Escape London {"position":"1200,200","size":"100,100"}

Lyra runs through London's streets with Pan beating his wings above her. Magisterium agents give chase, but dark alleys are the territory of a girl who grew up scaling Oxford's rooftops.

A group of gyptians find her by the Thames. They recognize her instantly. *"You're the Jordan College girl? Ma Costa's been expecting you."*

They pull her onto a boat and vanish into the river.

[[Board the gyptian ship->The Gyptian Ship]]


:: Escape With Everyone {"position":"3550,100","size":"100,100"}

Lyra leads the children down the central corridor. The most dangerous route — and the fastest.

(if: $allies >= 5)[
The gyptians storm through the main doors just as Lyra reaches them. John Faa, rifle in hand, bellows: *"Children first! Get them all out!"*

(if: $foundWitch is true)[
Above, the witches of Serafina Pekkala's clan loose arrows at the tower guards. The snow fills with winged shadows.
]

Every child gets out. Every single one.

(goto: "Good Ending")

](else:)[
Lyra reaches the main doors but there aren't enough reinforcements. Some children make it out. Others are held back by the guards.

Pan says what Lyra can't: *"We can't save them all. Not today."*

(goto: "Bittersweet Ending")
]


:: Escape With Roger {"position":"3550,300","size":"100,100"}

Lyra seizes Roger's hand and drags him into the ventilation shaft. Pan and Salcilia — if she still exists — follow close behind.

They emerge into the Arctic night. Snow stings their faces. They run toward the gyptian camp.

They're safe. But the other children are still inside.

(if: $allies >= 5)[
The gyptians assault the station as Lyra and Roger flee. Not every child will be saved. But many will.

(goto: "Bittersweet Ending")
](else:)[
Lyra looks back at the lights of Bolvangar, blazing against the Arctic dark.

*"We'll come back for them,"* she says, though she doesn't know how.

(goto: "Bittersweet Ending")
]


:: Examine Alethiometer {"position":"550,350","size":"100,100"}

Lyra turns the alethiometer in her hands. It's golden, heavy, the size of a large compass, with thirty-six symbols engraved around its face and four hands that swing freely.

Pan leans in as a mouse. *"How does it work?"*

Lyra turns the wheels. Three symbols align. The long hand begins to move, settling on: **the Anchor**, **the Skull**, and **(either: "the Serpent", "the Hourglass", "the Thunderbolt")**.

*"I think it's trying to tell me about danger,"* Lyra murmurs.

How does she read it?

[[The danger comes from the Magisterium — we need to run->Correct Reading 1]]
[[Someone close to her is in mortal danger->Wrong Reading 1]]


:: Find the Gyptians {"position":"1050,300","size":"100,100"}

(set: $panState to "resolute")

Lyra slips out of Jordan College that same night. Pan flies ahead as an owl, guiding her through darkened streets to the canals.

The gyptians take her in cautiously. Ma Costa, a broad, warm woman whose own son Billy was taken by the Gobblers, brings Lyra aboard her boat.

*"We knew you'd come, child,"* says Ma Costa. *"The gyptians have been searching for the missing children for weeks. And you have something that can help us."*

Her eyes fall on the bulge in Lyra's pocket. The alethiometer.

(set: $allies to $allies + 1)

[[Board the gyptian ship->The Gyptian Ship]]


:: Finding Roger {"position":"2800,200","size":"100,100"}



Lyra pushes open the last door in the corridor and there he is: **Roger**.

Alive. His dæmon Salcilia leaps toward Pan in cat form, and the two dæmons press together.

*"Lyra!"* Roger throws his arms around her. *"I knew you'd come. I knew it."*

Her eyes burn. *"I promised I'd look after you."*

The relief lasts seconds. An alarm screams somewhere in the building. Running footsteps. And then a voice — soft, terrible, familiar:

*"Lyra, darling. Have you come to visit me?"*

**Mrs Coulter** stands at the end of the corridor, the golden monkey on her shoulder.

(if: $knowsMotherTruth is true)[
Lyra meets her eyes. *"I know who you are. I know you're my mother. And I know what you're doing here."*

Mrs Coulter's face drains of colour.
](else:)[
Lyra steps in front of Roger. *"I won't let you touch him."*

Mrs Coulter smiles. *"Lyra, there are so many things you don't know about yourself..."*
]

A guard grabs Roger and drags him toward the laboratory. Toward the machine.

[[The machine — NOW!->The Machine]]


:: Go with Coulter {"position":"1050,100","size":"100,100"}

(set: $coulterRoute to true)
(set: $panState to "uneasy")

London is a different world. Bright lights, elegant parties, expensive dresses. Mrs Coulter teaches Lyra to behave like a lady, but Pan watches the golden monkey with growing dread.

*"I don't like it,"* Pan whispers at night. *"That monkey watches me when he thinks I'm not looking."*

Days pass. Lyra notices visitors in Magisterium robes. One evening, she finds Mrs Coulter's study door ajar.

[[Search the study->Search the Study]]
[[Too risky — escape now->Escape London]]


:: Good Ending {"position":"3800,100","size":"100,100"}



# All the Children Home

Bolvangar burns behind them. Snow glitters with reflected flames and the green wash of the aurora borealis.

Lyra walks surrounded by children holding their dæmons close. Roger is at her side, Salcilia purring on his shoulder. Ma Costa weeps with joy.

Pan settles on Lyra's neck in ermine form. Calm. For the first time in weeks, calm.

*"We did it, Pan,"* Lyra whispers.

*"Yes,"* says Pan. *"But look."*

He points north, where the aurora blazes with unearthly intensity. And in the sky, Lyra sees what no one else can see: particles of Dust, falling like golden rain over all of them.

(if: $accuracy >= 2)[
The alethiometer vibrates in her pocket. She draws it out and the needles speak with a clarity she's never experienced. They tell her this is not the end. That Lord Asriel waits beyond the aurora. That her journey is only beginning.
]

*"Come on, Pan,"* says Lyra, her eyes on the northern lights. *"We've still got a long way to go."*


END — The Good Path
You showed the courage and determination of Lyra Belacqua.


(if: $foundWitch is true)[
*✦ You discovered the secret encounter with Serafina Pekkala.*
]
(if: $hasDocs is true)[
*✦ You discovered the secret documents in Jordan's cellars.*
]

(if: $foundWitch is true and $accuracy >= 2 and $sawBilly is true)[

---

But then the alethiometer vibrates with an intensity Lyra has never felt. Pan turns sharply. *"Lyra... do you feel that? The Dust is speaking to you."*

[[Step away from the camp...->Secret Ending]]
]


:: Jordan Cellars {"position":"550,500","size":"100,100"}

(set: $hasDocs to true)

While everyone goes up, Lyra goes down. The cellars of Jordan College are damp, dark, and smell of centuries. Pan shifts to cat form to see in the gloom.

At the end of a corridor she's never explored, she finds a locked door. An old padlock, easily defeated with a bent piece of wire — a trick the kitchen boys taught her.

Inside: a chamber lined with yellowed documents. Lyra reads fragments — reports on the earliest Dust experiments, dated decades before Bolvangar. And the most disturbing part: Jordan College was involved in the research from the beginning.

*"Lyra..."* Pan whispers, *"this is much bigger than we thought."*

She stuffs several documents inside her shirt.

[[Back to the rooftops->Jordan Rooftops]]


:: Jordan Rooftops {"position":"450,200","size":"100,100"}

Morning light pours across the rooftops of Jordan College. From up here Lyra can see all of Oxford — the spires, the canals where the gyptian boats are moored, the distant factory smoke.

Pan scrambles along the tiles in ermine form. *"Plenty to do today, Lyra. Where do we start?"*

A quiet moment. The last one for a while.

[[Eavesdrop on the scholars->Eavesdrop Scholars]]
[[Visit Roger in the kitchens->Visit Roger]]
[[Examine the alethiometer the Rector gave her->Examine Alethiometer]]
[[Explore the cellars beneath the college->Jordan Cellars]]

(if: (count: (history:), "Jordan Rooftops") >= 2)[

---

Pan freezes mid-stride. *"Lyra. Roger isn't in the kitchens. He isn't anywhere."*

A cold knot tightens in Lyra's stomach.

[[Something is very wrong->The Disappearance]]
]


:: Search the Study {"position":"1200,50","size":"100,100"}

(set: $allies to $allies + 1)

Pan keeps watch as a moth by the door. Lyra rifles through the drawers. She finds a map with **Bolvangar** circled in red, and a list of names. Children's names. Among them: **Roger Parslow**.

She also finds a folder stamped **"General Oblation Board."** The Gobblers. Mrs Coulter runs the Gobblers.

The golden monkey appears in the doorway. It seizes Pan — Lyra feels the violation like a fist in her chest. She smashes a paperweight into the monkey's face and runs.

[[Run for the canals->Escape London]]


:: Secret Ending {"position":"3800,500","size":"100,100"}



(if: $foundWitch is true and $accuracy >= 2 and $sawBilly is true)[

## The Reader of Dust

While the others rest, Lyra walks away from the camp alone. Pan follows in silence.

She sits in the snow and takes out the alethiometer. But this time she doesn't need to turn the wheels. The needles move on their own, and Lyra reads them the way you'd read an open book.

And then she sees it.

The Dust. Not as particles in a photograph, but as golden rain falling on everything — on her, on Pan, on the snow, on the whole world. It's beautiful. The most beautiful thing she has ever seen.

*"Lyra,"* Pan breathes, *"what is it?"*

*"It's what makes us us, Pan. It's what connects people to their dæmons. It's consciousness. It's... everything."*

Serafina Pekkala's words echo in her mind: *"Dust is what makes us human."*

Lyra understands. She isn't just a girl searching for her friend. She is the child of the prophecy. The one who reads truth without being taught. The one who will decide the fate of Dust.

Pan transforms. For a single moment, he takes the shape of something Lyra doesn't recognize — a creature from another world, luminous and strange. Then he's an ermine again.

*"I'm not ready to settle,"* Pan says.

*"No,"* says Lyra, smiling. *"Not yet. We've got too much living to do."*

She stands, brushes the snow from her coat, and looks north — where Lord Asriel waits. Where the worlds touch. Where everything begins.


✦ SECRET END — The Reader of Dust ✦
You discovered Lyra's true nature and her connection to Dust.
To reach this ending, you needed: the witch encounter, accurate alethiometer readings, and Billy Costa's story.


](else:)[

