# The Girl and the Dust

---

Night in Jordan College, Oxford. Lyra Belacqua is hiding inside the wardrobe of the Retiring Room — a place no child should ever enter.

Pantalaimon, her dæmon, trembles on her shoulder in the form of a moth. *"Lyra, someone's coming,"* he whispers. *"Footsteps. Many."*

The door swings open. She recognizes the Rector's voice — and another, deep and commanding, that she's never heard before. They're speaking about something called "Dust."

[[Stay hidden and listen->Stay Hidden]]
[[Try to slip out before they see her->Try to Escape]]


:: Stay Hidden {"position":"250,100","size":"100,100"}

(set: $allies to $allies + 1)
(set: $panState to "tense")

Lyra holds her breath. Through the crack in the wardrobe door, she sees the Rector accompanied by Lord Asriel — a tall man with fierce eyes and a snow leopard dæmon that fills the room with its presence.

Asriel projects photographs onto the wall. Frozen landscapes. Children. And something else: a strange rain of golden particles falling over human figures.

*"This is Dust,"* says Asriel. *"And the Magisterium will do anything to destroy it."*

Pan stiffens. *"What does he mean by anything?"* he breathes, barely audible.

Lyra hears a name: **Bolvangar**. And a word that chills her blood: **intercision**. The severing of a child from their dæmon.

When the scholars leave, Lyra climbs out of the wardrobe, trembling. She heard everything. She understands nothing. Yet.

The next morning, the Rector calls her aside. His hands tremble as he presses a golden instrument into her palms — an **alethiometer**. *"Keep this hidden, Lyra. It tells the truth, to those who know how to read it. You may need it before long."*

[[Go to the rooftops to think->Jordan Rooftops]]


:: The Disappearance {"position":"900,200","size":"100,100"}

Everything changes in a single morning.

Roger is gone.

Lyra searches the entire college — rooftops, kitchens, canals. Nothing. Pan flies over Oxford as a swallow, scanning every street. Nothing.

*"The Gobblers,"* Lyra says, with a cold fury she's never felt before. *"They've taken Roger."*

That same day, a dazzling woman arrives at Jordan College in a sleek black car. **Mrs Coulter**, with her golden monkey dæmon. She smiles as though the world belongs to her.

*"Lyra, darling,"* she says, voice like silk. *"I'd love for you to come live with me in London. There's so much I could teach you..."*

Before Lyra leaves, the Rector pulls her aside. *"The alethiometer I gave you — guard it with your life. Let no one know you have it. Especially not her."*

[[Accept Mrs Coulter's offer->Go with Coulter]]
[[Refuse her and find the gyptians->Find the Gyptians]]


:: The Escape {"position":"3400,200","size":"100,100"}


(set: $timer to 20)

The corridors of Bolvangar are in chaos. The alarm screams without pause. Lyra guides Roger and a group of children toward the exit.

Pan flies ahead as an owl, scouting.

*"Left!"* Pan shrieks. *"No — right! Guards on the left!"*



